highlightedText: 2-day journey to one of the most captivating cities in the world—Copenhagen!

text: 2-day journey to one of the most captivating cities in the world—Copenhagen!

The Changing of the Guard at Amalienborg Palace is free of charge.
Walking to Nyhavn also doesn't cost anything.
The ticket for The Little Mermaid statue costs 10€ per person. It's a popular attraction, so I recommend booking your tickets in advance.
The polar bear ride at Tivoli Gardens costs 15€ per person.
Visiting Copenhagen's flea markets like Thorvaldsens Plads Antique Market is free, but keep some cash for any interesting antiques you might want to buy.
The ticket for The National Museum of Denmark costs 3€ per person.

text: The city is well-connected by buses, trains, and metro. However, one of the most convenient ways to travel around the city is by the T4 train line. It's fast, efficient, and can take you to most of the major attractions, including the airport.
